The federal government has filed fresh terrorism charges against the leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB) Nnamdi Kanu. In the fresh charges filed at a Federal High Court sitting in Abuja, the Federal Government increased the counts in the initial charge it preferred against Kanu. Kanu has been in detention since his he was re-arrested and brought back from Kenya into the country. Federal Govt Wants Nnamdi Kanu’s Motion Dismissed Initially, he was facing a seven-count treasonable felony charge but will now face a fresh 15-count amended charge marked FHC/ABJ/CR/383/2015, and signed by the Director of Public Prosecution (DPP), M. B. Abubakar. The charge was amended barely 24 hours before the scheduled commencement of hearing by Justice Binta Nyako. Details later….    